BeastieMon — lightweight FreeBSD system monitoring daemon.

Collects CPU, memory, disk I/O, network, filesystem, and temperature
metrics every second and serves them through a self-contained web
dashboard with live graphs (uPlot) and a command-line tool (beastie).

No authentication — bind to localhost and proxy through nginx/haproxy
if LAN or TLS access is required.

WWW: https://github.com/yourorg/beastiemon
